selecting for things on document object:
1.) document.querySelector("")
create new elements on a document object:
2.) document.createElement("")

==================================

On the Element object, we can set the textContent
example: name of an Element object is "listItem"

3.)listItem.textContent = "set it to something"

example: name of an Element object is "image"
Now, set the Attribute src = "https...."
4.) image.setAttribute("src", "https...")

Now set the attribute of listItem to class = "green"
5a.) listItem.className="green"
5b.) listItem.setAttribute("class", "green")

=======================================

To append a child element to a parent element:
1.)  select for the parent element: var ul = document.querySelector("ul")
2.)  append the child element to the parent using:
        ul.appendChild(listItem)
